# ZYNQ Peer

ZYNQ Peer is a lightweight WebRTC wrapper built on top of PeerJS.

It enables:

- ЁЯУб Peer-to-peer messaging
- ЁЯОе Video & audio streaming
- ЁЯФБ Automatic reconnection
- тЪб Rate-limited messaging

## Quick Start

```js
const peer = ZYNQ.peer.get('remote-id');

peer.on('open', () => {
  peer.send('Hello ЁЯСЛ');
});

peer.on('data', console.log);

peer.connect();
```

# Methods

## Connection

```js
peer.connect(remoteId);
peer.close();
peer.destroy();
```

## Messaging

```js
peer.send('Hello');
```

## Media

```js
await peer.getStream();
```

---

## Static

```js
ZYNQ.peer.get(id);
ZYNQ.peer.destroyAll();
```

# Favorites & History

## Favorites

```js
games.toggleFavorite('game-id');
games.isFavorite('game-id');
```

## History

```js
games.addToHistory('game-id');
games.getHistory();
games.clearHistory();
```

- Stored in `localStorage`
- History capped at 50 items
